Section 2: Additional Use Grant

The following uses of the Licensed Work are permitted in production
environments without a commercial license:

2.1 Permitted Uses (No Commercial License Required)

- Lancelot Ecosystem Use. Integration with the Lancelot governed autonomy
  platform and its associated ecosystem products (including TradeOS and Ada)
  developed by the Licensor.

- Personal Non-Commercial Use. Use of the Licensed Work for personal,
  non-commercial purposes by individual developers on their own machines,
  provided no revenue is generated directly or indirectly from such use.
  Individual installations of the Licensed Work on personal machines by
  distinct users each qualify independently as Personal Non-Commercial Use
  and are not aggregated for purposes of the Scale Deployment threshold in
  Section 2.2.

- Academic and Research Use. Use of the Licensed Work in academic research,
  educational institutions, and non-profit organizations, provided results
  and findings may be published but the Licensed Work itself is not
  redistributed in a commercial product.

- Evaluation and Testing. Use of the Licensed Work for internal evaluation,
  testing, prototyping, proof-of-concept development, benchmarking, and
  security auditing, provided such use does not serve production workloads
  or end users.

- Open Source Projects. Use of the Licensed Work in open source projects
  licensed under OSI-approved licenses, provided the open source project
  does not offer a paid/commercial version that incorporates the Licensed
  Work, and provided the open source project itself is not primarily a
  wrapper, reskin, or thin abstraction over the Licensed Work's core
  functionality.

2.2 Restricted Uses (Commercial License Required)

The following uses require a separate commercial license agreement with the
Licensor:

- Commercial Agent Runtimes. Incorporating, embedding, bundling, or linking
  the Licensed Work (or any substantial portion thereof) into any commercial
  software product, agent runtime, agent framework, automation platform, or
  AI system that is sold, licensed, offered as a service, or otherwise
  distributed for commercial purposes.

- Service Offerings. Offering the functionality of the Licensed Work, in
  whole or in part, as a service to third parties, whether as a standalone
  service, as part of a platform, or integrated into a larger offering. This
  includes but is not limited to: hosted agent control services, remote
  desktop automation services, cloud-based app interaction platforms, and
  managed automation services.

- Competing Products. Offering the Licensed Work, or a substantially similar
  product derived from the Licensed Work, as a competing product, library,
  SDK, or framework that provides framework-level application hooking,
  unified application control interfaces, or multi-framework introspection
  capabilities.

- Scale Deployment. Using the Licensed Work in any product or service
  deployed to more than twenty-five (25) unique end users or devices without
  a commercial license, regardless of whether the product or service is
  offered for a fee.

- Enterprise Internal Use. Using the Licensed Work to provide internal
  automation, tooling, or agent capabilities within a commercial
  organization where such use directly or indirectly generates revenue,
  reduces costs, or provides operational advantage, and where the
  organization has more than twenty-five (25) employees.

2.3 Clarifications

- The determination of whether a use is "commercial" shall be interpreted
  broadly. If the Licensed Work contributes to revenue generation, cost
  reduction, or competitive advantage for a for-profit entity, it is
  considered commercial use.

- Using the Licensed Work to build, train, or improve a competing product
  constitutes a Restricted Use even if the Licensed Work itself is not
  distributed.

- The Licensor reserves the right to grant additional use permissions on a
  case-by-case basis through written agreements.

- If you are uncertain whether your intended use requires a commercial
  license, contact the Licensor for clarification.


Section 3: Patent Notice

The Licensed Work is the subject of one or more pending patent applications
filed by the Licensor. This License does not grant any express or implied
license under any patent claims owned or controlled by the Licensor, except
to the extent necessary to exercise the rights expressly granted in Section
1 and Section 2 above.

Without limiting the foregoing, the following aspects of the Licensed Work
are covered by pending patent applications and may not be independently
reimplemented, reproduced, or practiced without a separate patent license
from the Licensor:

- The framework detection system for identifying UI toolkit composition of
  running applications through library signature analysis, process metadata
  inspection, and binary structure evaluation.

- The unified API abstraction layer that normalizes heterogeneous
  framework-specific introspection interfaces into a single standardized
  control interface.

- The hook injection and management system for establishing runtime
  introspection connections to applications across multiple UI frameworks
  through framework-specific plugin architectures.

- The multi-method control router that dynamically selects and falls back
  between control methods (direct API, framework hooks, accessibility APIs,
  vision-based control) based on availability, reliability, and capability
  assessment.

- The integrated system combining framework detection, hook management,
  unified abstraction, and fallback routing into a cohesive application
  control runtime.

These patent claims are independent of and additional to the copyright
protections of this License. Expiration of this License's restrictions on
the Change Date does not grant any patent license beyond what is stated
here.


